        <font color="white" face="Verdana, Arial, Helvetica" size="2"> Reegor,</P><P>Sadly I do know what I'm talking about. It was posted this was live ... it was NEVER posted this was intentional. No patch message, no anything.</P><P>I'm an avid gamer of MANY years. MUDs for at least 6 years, BBS games for at least 2 years before that, AO, AC, DAoC, and EQ. I've been around the multiplayer gaming block and yes, I'm very familiar with the benefits of level restrictions on items (and rent items, and game unique items ...etc).</P><P>I'm not saying EQ shouldn't have done this from the beginning. That's a definite. And honestly if they do, I'm not one of the guys this kind of thing would really affect. But you HAVE to look at the flip side. This is one item. Imagine if hundreds of items "nerfed" like this, and I'm sure that's what the point would be. If VI did this it would absolutely be a thorn in the side of all the happy, paying, uber twinks out there. They wouldn't be able to PL a new character as easily and wear that super item with super stats. And in a game this "aged", it would be as the previous poster said so nicely ... a death blow. A LOT of people would leave. Me? Probably not ... I need something to play. :)</P><P>In addition, what I was saying above is ... I'll believe it when I actually see it. Will it affect me? Not really. Will I leave the game? No. Will it affect the lower game in a balance and perhaps make the platinum poor EQ'ers happy? Yes. Will that in turn bring new customers ... probably not. </P><P>And most importantly will this, if it's actually true, cause paying customers to leave due to frustration? YES, most definately.</P><P></P><P>- Haytred, 38 DE Necro, Bristlebane</P><P>Warlock Miyagi says, "Show me sand da floor .... show me buff da pet."</P><P><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=157027" target="_blank">http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=157027</a></P><P>Edited by - Haytred on 04/11/2002  17:34:00<a hre